		<div id="comment_body_64176523"><p>The filesystem had a lot of innovation.  However, times change.  Xiafs was awesome for its time as well, but ext2 eventually rendered that obsolete.  These days, ZFS or btrfs are probably the best general purpose filesystems going for Linux, with ext4 and XFS also useful.</p><p>As far as I know, ReiserFS doesn't have any checksumming or scrubbing available, which is something needed for modern filesystems.</p></div>
	</div>

