		<div id="comment_body_64177031">"Antisocial" is maybe not the best word to describe someone who does not enjoy social interactions. "Antisocial" originally referred to people who have a pathological personality disorder (sociopaths). Maybe Reiser is actually antisocial in that sense, I don't know. It doesn't sound like the poster you are replying to is a sociopath.
<br> <br>
But it is so frequently used to describe people who are merely unsociable that its meaning is shifting. But it still has the old meaning also. So it is kind of a fundamentall</div>
